jin\n*Kang Yo-hwan as Kim Sang-hyuk\n*Lee Se-na as Oh Chae-rin\n*[[Ryu Seung-soo]] as Kwon Yong-gook\n*Seon Jeon-hui as Kong Jin-sook\n\n==Musical theatre==\n''Winter Sonata'' marked its 10th year milestone with a staging of a new musical adaptation that ran from September 27, 2011 to March 18, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hong|first=Lucia|title=''Winter Sonata'' celebrates 10 year anniversary with new musical adaptation|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2011090209572052220|work=10Asia|date=2 September 2011|accessdate=2012-01-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Choi Ji Woo: 'I Miss Park Yong Ha'|url=http://english.kbs.co.kr/hallyu/gallery_view.html?No=1282|work=KBS Global|date=18 January 2012|accessdate=2012-01-19}}</ref> [[Yoon Seok-ho]] was the producer and art director, with stage direction by Yoo Hee-sung (''[[Mozart!]]'', ''Pimagol Love Song'') and musical score by Oh Eun-hee (''[[Dae Jang Geum#Musical|Dae Jang Geum]]'', ''[[Singin' in the Rain (musical)|Singin' in the Rain]]''). The leading role of Yoo-jin was portrayed by musical actress [[Choi Soo-jin]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Park|first=Hyun-min|title=Girls' Generation Watch ''Winter Sonata'' Musical|url=http://enewsworld.mnet.com/enews/contents.asp?idx=811|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130128224535/http://enewsworld.mnet.com/enews/contents.asp?idx=811|url-status=dead|archive-date=28 January 2013|work=enewsWorld|publisher=CJ E&M|date=9 October 2011|accessdate=2012-01-19}}</ref>\n\nThe ''Winter Sonata'' musical first premiered in 2006 in several cities in Japan, including Sapporo, Tokyo and Osaka, and popular crossover tenor Im Tae-kyung drew crowds.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Yong-sung|title=Television drama producer finds stage just as rewarding|url=http://www.hancinema.net/herald-interviewtelevision-drama-producer-finds-stage-just-as-rewarding-5227.html|work=[[The Korea Herald]] via [[Hancinema]]|accessdate=2013-03-19|date=13 February 2006}}</ref> It also completed a run in Busan and Seoul, from late 2010 to early 2011, with stage direction by Im Do-wan (''[[Woyzeck]]'') and musical score by Lee Ji-soo.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hong|first=Lucia|title=''Winter Sonata'' musical to open in Korea in December|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2011090209572052220|work=10Asia|date=16 June 2010|accessdate=2012-01-19}}</ref>\n\n===Cast===\n====2006====\n*Im Tae-kyung and Lee Sang-hyeon as Kang Joon-sang / Lee Min-hyung\n*Park Hong-joo and Im Kang-hee as Jeong Yoo-jin\n*Lee Pil-sung as Kim Sang-hyuk\n*Jiny as Oh Chae-rin\n*Lee Jin-kyu as Kwon Yong-gook\n*Kim Gyung-hwa as Kong Jin-sook\n*Shin Bok-ja as Kang Mi-hee, Joon-sang's mother\n*Yang Joon-mo as Spirit\n*Nam Moon-chul as Dr. Oh, Chae-rin's father\n\n====2011====\n*Kim Tae-han as Kang Joon-sang / Lee Min-hyung\n*Park Woo-ne and [[Choi Soo-jin]] as Jeong Yoo-jin\n*Jeong Jae-hong and Kim Gyeong-soo as Kim Sang-hyuk\n\n===Soundtrack===\n====2006====\n#\"Overture\n#\"Endless Song - performed by Park Hong-joo\n#\"My Great Proposal\" - performed by Lee Pil-sung\n#\"I Will be Always Waiting for You\" - performed by Lee Pil-sung\n#\"I'm Your Girl\" - performed by Jiny \n#\"Confusion\" - performed by Lee Sang-hyeon\n#\"Light of the Life\" - performed by Shin Bok-ja\n#\"Is This Love\" - performed by Im Tae-kyung\n#\"Can't Love Another Day + I Won't Alone\" - performed by Lee Sang-hyeon\n#\"For Your Memory\" - performed by Im Tae-kyung\n#\"Now I Remember\" - performed by Im Tae-kyung\n#\"Eternal Love\" - performed by Lee Sang-hyeong\n#\"Missing You\" - performed by Lee Pil-sung\n#\"Remember\" - performed by Lee Sang-hyeon\n#\"My Memory\" - performed by Im Tae-kyung\n\n==Manga==\nA [[manga|Japanese comic]] has also been published of this story, using photos of the series as covers.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Issue || ISBN || Published\n|-\n|1||{{ISBNT|4-7767-1329-2}}||2004-07-08\n|-\n|2||{{ISBNT|4-7767-1330-6}}||2004-07-08\n|-\n|3||{{ISBNT|4-7767-1331-4}}||2004-08-20\n|-\n|4||{{ISBNT|4-7767-1416-7}}||2004-10-20\